Playoffs and Finals
Each season’s playoffs followed the official IPL format (Qualifier 1 between #1 and #2; Eliminator between
#3 and #4; Qualifier 2 between loser of Q1 and winner of Eliminator; final between Q1 winner and Q2
winner). In 2024, KKR (1) beat SRH (2) in Qualifier 1, RR (3) and RCB (4) met in the Eliminator , RCB won to face
SRH again in Qualifier 2, and KKR beat SRH in the final. In 2025, PBKS (1) vs RCB (2) in Qualifier 1
(PBKS won), GT (3) vs MI (4) in Eliminator (GT won), RCB vs GT in Qualifier 2 (RCB won), and RCB beat PBKS in
the final .
Key final match highlights are noted above; award winners include:
- 2024: Orange Cap Virat Kohli (741 runs), Purple Cap Harshal Patel (24 wickets), MVP Sunil Narine
(482 runs, 17 wkts), Emerging Player Nitish Reddy (SRH).
-  2025:  Orange  Cap  Sai  Sudharsan  (759  runs),  Purple  Cap  Prasidh  Krishna  (25  wickets),  MVP
Suryakumar Yadav, Emerging Player Sai Sudharsan. Notably, RCB’s Krunal Pandya won Final Man of the
Match . Fair Play winners were SRH (2024) and CSK (2025). 
